verse.lines:
{lang-eng}O God! we see Thee in the Lamb
To be our hope, our joy, our rest;
The glories that compose Thy name
Standing engaged to make us blest.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Then, Oh! to us this grace afford,
That far from Thee we ne’er may move;
Our guard—the presence of the Lord;
Our joy—Thy perfect present love.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}This gives us ever to rejoice,
Turning to light our darkest days;
And lifts on high each feeble voice,
While we have breath to pray or praise{/lang-eng}
